-- Apranga, Baltic Retailer, Forecasts Sales Rising 7.6% This Year
-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 2012-01-02T14:16:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/apranga-baltic-retailer-forecasts-sales-rising-7-6-this-year.html
Apranga AB, the biggest Baltic
clothing retailer, expects sales to grow 7.6 percent this year
from 2011.  The retailer, which currently operates 121 stores in
Lithuania, Latvia and  Estonia , will add between 9 to 11 new
outlets this year and reconstruct another eight, the Vilnius-
based company said in a statement to the stock exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Milda Seputyte in Vilnius at 
 mseputyte@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  